            <paragraph><strong>RibbonTrailMesh</strong> represents a straight ribbon-shaped mesh with variable width. The ribbon is composed of a number of flat or cross-shaped sections, each with the same <reference internal="True" refid="class-ribbontrailmesh-property-section-length"><inline classes="std std-ref">section_length</inline></reference> and number of <reference internal="True" refid="class-ribbontrailmesh-property-section-segments"><inline classes="std std-ref">section_segments</inline></reference>. A <reference internal="True" refid="class-ribbontrailmesh-property-curve"><inline classes="std std-ref">curve</inline></reference> is sampled along the total length of the ribbon, meaning that the curve determines the size of the ribbon along its length.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>This primitive mesh is usually used for particle trails.</paragraph>
